and roll band," Bruce

00:30:27.759 --> 00:30:31.396
Springsteen once said, is
that "the narrative you tell

00:30:31.396 --> 00:30:34.532
together is bigger than
anyone could have told on

00:30:34.532 --> 00:30:38.169
your own." And for decades,
alongside the Big Man,

00:30:38.169 --> 00:30:41.906
Little Steven, a Jersey girl
named Patti, and all the men

00:30:41.906 --> 00:30:45.143
and women of the E Street
Band, Bruce Springsteen has

00:30:45.143 --> 00:30:48.313
been carrying the rest of us
on his journey, asking us

00:30:48.313 --> 00:30:52.717
all "what is the work for
us to do in our short time

00:30:52.717 --> 00:30:55.353
here." I am the President.

00:30:55.353 --> 00:30:56.120
But he is The Boss.

00:30:56.120 --> 00:30:58.056
(laughter)

00:30:58.056 --> 00:31:02.927
And pushing 70, he's still
laying down four-hour live

00:31:02.927 --> 00:31:06.664
sets -- if you have been
at them, he is working.

00:31:06.664 --> 00:31:10.902
"Fire-breathing rock 'n'
roll." So I thought twice

00:31:10.902 --> 00:31:13.571
about giving him a medal
named for freedom because we

00:31:13.571 --> 00:31:17.842
hope he remains, in his
words, a "prisoner of rock

00:31:17.842 --> 00:31:20.345
'n' roll" for years to come.

00:31:20.345 --> 00:31:24.916
So, I told you, this is
like a really good class.

00:31:24.916 --> 00:31:25.917
(laughter)

00:31:25.917 --> 00:31:27.919
Ladies and gentlemen, I want
you all to give it up for

00:31:27.919 --> 00:31:30.788
the recipients of the 2016
Presidential Medal of Freedom.

00:31:30.788 --> 00:31:42.200
(applause)

00:31:44.669 --> 00:31:49.774
It is a good group.

00:31:49.774 --> 00:31:56.514
All right.

00:31:56.514 --> 00:31:59.284
Now we actually got
to give them medals.

00:31:59.284 --> 00:32:02.987
So please be patient.

00:32:02.987 --> 00:32:05.356
We are going to have my
military aide read

00:32:05.356 --> 00:32:07.458
the citations.

00:32:07.458 --> 00:32:10.328
Each one of them will come
up and receive the medals,

00:32:10.328 --> 00:32:12.263
and then we'll wrap
up the program.

00:32:12.263 --> 00:32:12.864
Okay.

00:32:12.864 --> 00:32:15.400
Let's hit it.

00:32:15.400 --> 00:32:17.001
Military Aide:
Kareem Abdul-Jabbar.

00:32:17.001 --> 00:32:19.270
(applause)

00:32:38.289 --> 00:32:44.062
An iconic basketball player
who revolutionized the sport

00:32:44.062 --> 00:32:46.798
with his all-around play and
signature skyhook, Kareem

00:32:46.798 --> 00:32:50.301
Abdul-Jabbar is a 19-time
All-Star, a 6-time world

00:32:50.301 --> 00:32:53.838
champion, and the leading
scorer in NBA history.

00:32:53.838 --> 00:32:56.140
Adding to his achievements
on the court he also left

00:32:56.140 --> 00:32:59.043
his mark off of it,
advocating for civil rights,

00:32:59.043 --> 00:33:02.780
cancer research, science
education, and social justice.

00:33:02.780 --> 00:33:04.882
In doing so, Kareem
Abdul-Jabbar leaves a

00:33:04.882 --> 00:33:08.119
towering legacy of
compassion, faith, and

00:33:08.119 --> 00:33:10.555
service to others -- a
legacy based not only on the

00:33:10.555 --> 00:33:12.957
strength and grace of his
athleticism, but on the

00:33:12.957 --> 00:33:15.426
sharpness of his mind and
the size of his heart.

00:33:15.426 --> 00:33:18.196
(applause)

00:33:45.189 --> 00:33:48.593
Turk Cobell, accepting
on behalf of his mother,

00:33:48.593 --> 00:33:51.329
Elouise C. Cobell Yellowbird Woman.

00:33:51.329 --> 00:33:54.399
(applause)

00:34:01.639 --> 00:34:04.475
A member of the Blackfeet
Nation, Elouise Cobell spent

00:34:04.475 --> 00:34:06.844
