As a teenage refugee from
Cuba, Eduardo Padrón came to

00:50:18.348 --> 00:50:20.784
the United States to pursue
the American Dream, and he

00:50:20.784 --> 00:50:23.687
has spent his life making
that dream real for others.

00:50:23.687 --> 00:50:25.689
As president of the
community college he once

00:50:25.689 --> 00:50:27.958
attended, his thoughtful
leadership and commitment to

00:50:27.958 --> 00:50:31.228
education have transformed
Miami Dade College into one

00:50:31.228 --> 00:50:33.730
of the premier learning
institutions in the country,

00:50:33.730 --> 00:50:35.766
earning him praise
around the world.

00:50:35.766 --> 00:50:38.001
His personal story and
lasting professional

00:50:38.001 --> 00:50:40.871
influence prove that success
need not be determined by

00:50:40.871 --> 00:50:43.974
our background, but by our
dedication to others and our

00:50:43.974 --> 00:50:47.377
passion for creating America
that is as inclusive as it

00:50:47.377 --> 00:50:48.445
is prosperous.

00:50:48.445 --> 00:50:51.214
(applause)

00:51:06.563 --> 00:51:07.731
Robert Redford.

00:51:07.731 --> 00:51:10.333
(applause)

00:51:19.609 --> 00:51:22.145
Robert Redford has
captivated audiences from

00:51:22.145 --> 00:51:24.815
both sides of the camera
through entertaining motion

00:51:24.815 --> 00:51:28.218
pictures that often explore
vital social, political, and

00:51:28.218 --> 00:51:29.486
historical themes.

00:51:29.486 --> 00:51:32.222
His lifelong advocacy on
behalf of preserving our

00:51:32.222 --> 00:51:35.525
environment will prove as
an enduring legacy as his

00:51:35.525 --> 00:51:38.395
award-winning films, as will
his pioneering support for

00:51:38.395 --> 00:51:40.664
independent filmmakers
across America.

00:51:40.664 --> 00:51:43.033
His art and activism
continue to shape our

00:51:43.033 --> 00:51:46.603
Nation's cultural heritage,
inspiring millions to laugh,

00:51:46.603 --> 00:51:49.005
cry, think, and change.

00:51:49.005 --> 00:51:51.908
(applause)

00:52:10.594 --> 00:52:11.328
Diana Ross.

00:52:11.328 --> 00:52:13.630
(laughter and applause)

00:52:29.346 --> 00:52:33.383
A daughter of Detroit, Diana
Ross helped create the sound

00:52:33.383 --> 00:52:35.685
of Motown with
her iconic voice.

00:52:35.685 --> 00:52:38.255
From her groundbreaking work
with The Supremes to a solo

00:52:38.255 --> 00:52:40.924
career that has spanned
decades, she has influenced

00:52:40.924 --> 00:52:43.927
generations of young artists
and shaped our Nation's

00:52:43.927 --> 00:52:45.695
musical landscape.

00:52:45.695 --> 00:52:47.964
In addition to a GRAMMY©
Lifetime Achievement Award

00:52:47.964 --> 00:52:50.534
and countless musical
accolades, Diana Ross has

00:52:50.534 --> 00:52:52.869
distinguished herself as
an actor, earning an Oscar

00:52:52.869 --> 00:52:55.572
nomination and a
Golden Globe Award.

00:52:55.572 --> 00:52:58.575
With over 25 albums,
unforgettable hit singles,

00:52:58.575 --> 00:53:01.044
and live performances that
continue to captivate

00:53:01.044 --> 00:53:04.314
audiences around the world,
Diana Ross still

00:53:04.314 --> 00:53:05.181
reigns supreme.

00:53:05.181 --> 00:53:07.250
(applause)

00:53:39.149 --> 00:53:40.283
Next up, Vin Scully.

00:53:40.283 --> 00:53:42.819
(laughter and applause)

00:53:52.295 --> 00:53:54.364
With a voice that
transcended a sport and

00:53:54.364 --> 00:53:56.766
transformed a profession,
Vin Scully narrated

00:53:56.766 --> 00:53:59.736
America's pastime for
generations of fans.

00:53:59.736 --> 00:54:02.038
Known to millions as the
soundtrack of summer, he

00:54:02.038 --> 00:54:05.742
found time to teach us
about life and love while

00:54:05.742 --> 00:54:09.479
chronicling routine plays
and historic heroics.

00:54:09.479 --> 00:54:11.915
In victory and in defeat,
his colorful accounts

00:54:11.915 --> 00:54:13.984
reverberated through the
bleachers, across the

00:54:13.984 --> 00:54:16.786
airwaves, and into our
homes and imaginations.

00:54:16.786 --> 00:54:19.856
He is an American treasure
and a beloved storyteller,

00:54:19.856 --> 00:54:22.292
and our country's gratitude
for Vin Scully is as

00:54:22.292 --> 00:54:24.494
profound as his
love for the game.

00:54:24.494 --> 00:54:27.163
(applause)

00:55:01.564 --> 00:55:02.899
Bruce F. Springsteen.

00:55:02.899 --> 00:55:05.268
(applause)

00:55:14.110 --> 00:55:17.313
As a songwriter, a
humanitarian, America's Rock

00:55:17.313 --> 00:55:19.315
and Roll laureate, and
New Jersey's greatest

00:55:19.315 --> 00:55:21.685
ambassador, Bruce
Springsteen is, quite

00:55:21.685 --> 00:55:22.919
simply, The Boss.

00:55:22.919 --> 00:55:24.354
(laughter)

00:55:24.354 --> 00:55:26.189
Through stories about
ordinary people, from

00:55:26.189 --> 00:55:28.858
Vietnam veterans to steel
workers, his songs capture

00:55:28.858 --> 00:55:31.628
the pain and the promise of
the American experience.

00:55:31.628 --> 00:55:34.597
With his legendary E Street
Band, Bruce Springsteen

00:55:34.597 --> 00:55:37.367
leaves everything on stage
in epic, communal live

00:55:37.367 --> 00:55:40.136
performances that have
rocked audiences for decades.

00:55:40.136 --> 00:55:43.373
With empathy and honesty, he
holds up a mirror to who we

00:55:43.373 --> 00:55:46.910
are -- as Americans chasing
our dreams, and as human

00:55:46.910 --> 00:55:48.912
beings trying to
do the right thing.

00:55:48.912 --> 00:55:50.914
There's a place for everyone
in Bruce

00:55:50.914 --> 00:55:52.115
Springsteen's America.

00:55:52.115 --> 00:55:54.551
(applause)

00:56:21.678 --> 00:56:22.512
Cicely Tyson.

00:56:22.512 --> 00:56:24.848
(applause)

00:56:42.398 --> 00:56:45.502
For sixty years, Cicely
Tyson has graced the screen

00:56:45.502 --> 00:56:47.971
and the stage, enlightening
us with her groundbreaking

00:56:47.971 --> 00:56:51.741
characters and calls to
conscience, humility, and hope.

00:56:51.741 --> 00:56:54.210
Her achievements as an
actor, her devotion to her

00:56:54.210 --> 00:56:57.113
faith, and her commitment to
advancing equality for all

00:56:57.113 --> 00:57:00.250
Americans-especially women
of color -- have touched

00:57:00.250 --> 00:57:02.752
audiences of multiple
generations.

00:57:02.752 --> 00:57:05.255
From "The Autobiography
of Miss Jane Pittman," to

00:57:05.255 --> 00:57:09.993
"Sounder," to "The Trip to
Bountiful," Cicely Tyson's

00:57:09.993 --> 00:57:12.629
performances illuminate the
character of our people and

00:57:12.629 --> 00:57:14.831
the extraordinary
possibilities of America.

00:57:14.831 --> 00:57:17.634
(applause)

00:57:52.101 --> 00:57:58.107
The President: So, just on a
personal note, part of the

00:57:58.107 --> 00:58:02.679
reason that these events are
so special to me is because

00:58:02.679 --> 00:58:07.917
everybody on this stage
has touched me in a very

00:58:07.917 --> 00:58:13.122
powerful, personal way --
in ways that they probably

00:58:13.122 --> 00:58:15.225
couldn't imagine.

00:58:15.225 --> 00:58:18.027
Whether it was having been
inspired by a song, or a

00:58:18.027 --> 00:58:31.507
game, or a story, or a film,
or a monument, or in the

00:58:31.507 --> 00:58:33.376
case of Newt Minow
introducing me to Michelle --

00:58:33.376 --> 00:58:36.946
(laughter)

00:58:36.946 --> 00:58:44.654
-- these are folks who have
helped make me who I am and

00:58:44.654 --> 00:58:50.159
think about my presidency,
and what also makes them

00:58:50.159 --> 00:58:52.695
special is, this is America.

00:58:52.695 --> 00:58:58.635
And it's useful when you
think about this incredible

00:58:58.635 --> 00:59:03.907
collection of people to
realize that this is what

00:59:03.907 --> 00:59:06.509
makes us the greatest
nation on Earth.

00:59:06.509 --> 00:59:07.176
Not because of what we --

00:59:07.176 --> 00:59:09.112
(applause)

00:59:19.389 --> 00:59:23.927
Not because of our
differences, but because, in

00:59:23.927 --> 00:59:27.263
our difference, we find
something common to share.

00:59:27.263 --> 00:59:29.365
And what a glorious
thing that is.

00:59:29.365 --> 00:59:32.969
What a great gift
that is to America.

00:59:32.969 --> 00:59:37.040
So I want all of you
to enjoy the wonderful

00:59:37.040 --> 00:59:40.310
reception that will be
taking place afterwards.

00:59:40.310 --> 00:59:43.112
Michelle and I have to get
back to work, unfortunately,

00:59:43.112 --> 00:59:44.514
but I hear the food
is pretty good.

00:59:44.514 --> 00:59:45.748
(laughter)

00:59:45.748 --> 00:59:49.118
And I would like all of you
to give one big rousing

00:59:49.118 --> 00:59:53.556
round of applause to our
2016 honorees for the

00:59:53.556 --> 00:59:56.492
Presidential
Medal of Freedom.

00:59:56.492 --> 00:59:57.360
Give it up.

00:59:57.360 --> 00:59:58.861
(applause)

